args: You are working quite diligently,\nPrincess Sharena. Lance training, is it?
I heard the treats I received the other day\nwere made by your hand, so I wished to\nexpress my gratitude in person.
You came all this way just to say that?\nHa ha! Perhaps I should be thanking you!
But more to the matter at hand—your\nlance skills are nothing to scoff at.\nDid you study under a master?
My teacher was a man named Zacharias.\nHe was an old friend of my brother and\nme, and a member of the Order of Heroes.
He WAS a member? My apologies.\nI did not mean to open old wounds.
Oh, it's all right. Don't worry about—
Guys! GUYYYYYYS! We got fiends\nattacking a village, guyyyyyys!
I shall rally the others at once!

Dude, there ARE no others! It's just you!
Everyone else is out dealing with the
fiends popping outta those space hole
thingies.
In that case, Princess Sharena, I fear\nI must beg your aid in this matter.
Of course. We'll depart at once.
...Fie, but there are far more fiends here\nthan I anticipated. If we don't act quickly,\nthe casualties will be terrible indeed.
I will divert the fiends' attention while\nyou lead the villagers to safety.
I cannot permit you to take on\nso many fiends at once!

Even our combined might cannot hope
to stop all of these fiends, Elisanne.
Our only hope is to have one of us
serve as a distraction.
Though it pains me, I hear the truth of\nyour words. Let us do as you suggest.
But if you get even the slightest sense\nthat the danger is overwhelming,\nyou must promise to call for me!
Come, fiends! Meet your true adversary!
*pant* I'll be honest... This isn't going...\nquite as well as I'd hoped...
But I'll not be laid low so easily!\nIf I can just buy a little more time,\nall the villagers will be able to flee!
I believe that was the last one.\nAre you hurt, Princess Sharena?
I'm fine, thanks to your good work.

I am pleased you are well, but that was
just the kind of dangerous situation
where I asked you to call out for me.
Why did you not do so?
Because it would have delayed\nthe evacuation of the villagers.
Perhaps I underestimated the situation,\nbut I did not wish to trouble you.
I understand, but would think it\na failure of your priorities if\nthey led to your injury—or worse.

If you agree that we are comrades—which
I dearly hope you do—then I would have
you turn to me whenever you are in need.
There can be no holding back.
Were my words overly harsh, Princess?\nI apologize if so.

No, you're right, of course. And if I'm
honest, I'm really happy that you think
of us as comrades. You can count on me
to hew to that relationship in the future.
We are comrades who fight alongside\none another. If ever you find yourself\nin a dark moment, know I will be there.
However, I wonder if you might consider\nme a friend as well as a comrade?
Oh, that makes me so happy!
